The paper deals with channel estimation in millimeter wave (mmWave) MIMO communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of hybrid precoders and combiners in mmWave MIMO systems is also a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper proposes compressed-sensing-based strategies for channel estimation, which is a technique related to signal processing (cs.SP) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with a frequency-selective mmWave channel model, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT).
